WEBVTT

00:01.771 --> 00:03.955
Kids, I bought the
house we live in now way back

00:03.956 --> 00:05.823
before I ever met your mother.

00:05.824 --> 00:08.659
It needed a lot of work,
but I had a vision for it.

00:08.660 --> 00:10.327
Vintage rolltop desk here.

00:10.328 --> 00:11.912
I haven't decided
whether to put the fern

00:11.913 --> 00:13.314
on the right or the left side,

00:13.315 --> 00:15.416
but you know, sometimes
you just gotta wing it. Right?

00:15.417 --> 00:16.584
Left side.

00:16.585 --> 00:17.751
Oh, and right outside,

00:17.752 --> 00:20.004
I want to put up a
basketball hoop for the kids.

00:20.005 --> 00:21.422
- Huh?
- Ted.

00:21.423 --> 00:23.591
This is your seduction lounge.

00:23.592 --> 00:25.426
Sex swing there,

00:25.427 --> 00:27.328
vibrating Jell-O pit
right there,

00:27.329 --> 00:29.697
rotating Vietnamese Shame Wheel
right here.

00:30.332 --> 00:31.799
Don't ask; you're not ready.

00:31.800 --> 00:34.535
And that basketball hoop?

00:34.536 --> 00:37.104
Outdoor stripper pole.

00:37.105 --> 00:39.340
We'll just tell the ladies
to be careful in the winter.

00:39.341 --> 00:42.476
You think a tongue stuck
to a frozen pole is bad...

00:42.477 --> 00:46.614
Hey. Barney, let's go
outside for a second.

00:46.615 --> 00:48.365
We have a confession.

00:48.366 --> 00:51.218
This wasn't really about
seeing Ted's house.

00:51.219 --> 00:53.220
It's an intervention.

00:53.221 --> 00:54.488
Oh, thank God.

00:54.489 --> 00:55.856
I'll go first.

00:55.857 --> 00:57.825
Ted, this house you bought
for your hypothetical family

00:57.826 --> 00:59.059
is super weird.

00:59.060 --> 01:01.061
We talk about it all the time
behind your back.

01:01.062 --> 01:02.847
Yeah. This intervention
isn't for me.

01:02.848 --> 01:04.197
It's for you.

01:04.199 --> 01:06.400
Why did Barney
need an intervention?

01:06.401 --> 01:08.435
It all started
a few nights earlier.

01:08.436 --> 01:09.770
Barney, I can't believe

01:09.771 --> 01:11.889
your giant TV is broken.
It's March Madness.

01:11.890 --> 01:13.974
Okay, uh, I think I see
what the problem is.

01:13.975 --> 01:15.476
Barney, can you grab me
a screwdriver?

01:15.477 --> 01:16.744
Sure thing.

01:16.745 --> 01:18.646
Luis. Barney Stinson, 12 H.

01:18.647 --> 01:20.881
I got a hundred bucks if you can
be here in five. Thanks.

01:20.882 --> 01:23.317
You call the super
for a screwdriver?

01:23.318 --> 01:25.553
Yeah... here's the thing
about me and tools...

01:25.554 --> 01:28.322
the only one I know how to use
is attached to me,

01:28.323 --> 01:30.925
and I am not going to try
putting it in the TV.

01:30.926 --> 01:32.293
Again.

01:32.294 --> 01:34.245
Okay, that's ridiculous.

01:34.246 --> 01:36.196
Everyone should know
how to use tools.

01:37.415 --> 01:40.501
Well, here's our
screwdriver now.

01:45.040 --> 01:47.808
Guys, I'm
pretty sure that's not Luis,

01:47.809 --> 01:49.143
but I can't be certain.

01:49.144 --> 01:50.477
Someone introduce yourself.

01:51.680 --> 01:54.548
Barney, I...

01:54.549 --> 01:57.117
I got your letter.

02:00.155 --> 02:02.323
Dad?

02:02.400 --> 02:06.324
Transcript by Addic7ed.com

02:06.325 --> 02:10.324
www.addic7ed.com

02:17.902 --> 02:19.569
I can't believe Barney
is talking to his dad right now.

02:19.570 --> 02:20.770
Yeah, what do you say

02:20.771 --> 02:22.172
after three decades
of not seeing each other?

02:22.173 --> 02:24.024
"So, how 'bout those

02:24.025 --> 02:25.959
last 30 Super Bowls"?

02:25.960 --> 02:27.093
Okay, now I feel bad

02:27.094 --> 02:29.129
about making fun of him
for the tool thing.

02:29.130 --> 02:31.464
My dad was the one
who taught me all that stuff.

02:31.465 --> 02:34.234
Well, to be fair, everyone has
some glaring gap in knowledge,

02:34.235 --> 02:36.336
something really obvious
you somehow never learned.

02:36.337 --> 02:38.138
Okay, but a screwdriver?

02:38.139 --> 02:40.073
Come on, I don't have any gaps
that fundamental.

02:40.074 --> 02:43.210
Really? I seem to recall...

02:43.211 --> 02:45.095
Daniel Burnham was an architect

02:45.096 --> 02:47.080
whose ever-shifting style
and aesthetic

02:47.081 --> 02:49.749
made him a true architectural
chamma-leeon.

02:51.252 --> 02:52.619
And only the most
gifted chamma-leeon

02:52.620 --> 02:55.222
could've designed
classic beaux arts masterpieces

02:55.223 --> 02:58.825
right alongside
sleek modern flatirons.

02:58.826 --> 03:00.594
His name might as well have been

03:00.595 --> 03:03.813
Daniel Chamma-leeon.

03:03.814 --> 03:05.482
Um, Professor?

03:05.483 --> 03:08.602
Uh, do you mean "chameleon"?

03:10.304 --> 03:15.175
Betty, I'm pretty sure it's
pronounced "chamma-leeon," so...

03:17.411 --> 03:19.663
Class dismissed.

03:19.664 --> 03:21.481
No homework. For a while.

03:21.482 --> 03:24.117
Okay, I learned that word
by reading it.

03:24.118 --> 03:26.286
That's how I've always
pronounced it.

03:26.287 --> 03:27.520
Oh, Ted, that wasn't easy.

03:27.521 --> 03:29.623
It took a lot of "ch-aracter"
to admit that.

03:29.624 --> 03:31.625
Okay, Scherbatsky.
You want to tussle?

03:31.626 --> 03:32.959
- I'll tussle.
- You want to tussle?

03:32.960 --> 03:34.794
- Let's tussle.
- Marine biologist.

03:34.795 --> 03:36.463
Please, no.

03:36.464 --> 03:38.164
So this really sucks, but

03:38.165 --> 03:40.600
I'm going to be in the North Pole
for the next three months.

03:40.601 --> 03:42.135
Seriously?

03:42.136 --> 03:43.370
The North Pole?

03:43.371 --> 03:45.188
Okay, pal, if you want
to break up with me,

03:45.189 --> 03:47.807
just tell it to me straight.
Don't pretend you're going

03:47.808 --> 03:49.576
someplace we all know
doesn't exist.

03:49.577 --> 03:51.778
Um, I'm going to be studying
the mating habits of...

03:51.779 --> 03:54.547
Of who? Santa's elves?
Rudolph?

03:54.548 --> 03:56.416
You know what?
I'm going on a trip, too, Scott.

03:56.417 --> 03:58.151
It, uh, starts in Narnia.

03:58.152 --> 03:59.886
It works its way up
to Candyland,

03:59.887 --> 04:02.122
and then, hey, congratulate me,

04:02.123 --> 04:04.224
because I'm the new Defense
Against the Dark Arts teacher

04:04.225 --> 04:07.093
at Hogwarts. Expelliarmus!

04:07.094 --> 04:09.696
Robin, the North Pole
is a real place.

04:09.697 --> 04:11.231
You know that, right?

04:13.167 --> 04:15.969
So... you want
to get pizza later? Or...

04:15.970 --> 04:17.771
I think we should break up.

04:17.772 --> 04:19.738
I still think about him
in the shower.

04:21.341 --> 04:23.643
- Hey. - Tell us everything.
How'd it go, bud?

04:23.644 --> 04:25.912
Where do I begin?

04:27.515 --> 04:29.482
- So, I'm not sure how to start this.
- Yeah.

04:31.183 --> 04:32.352
I think I need a drink.

04:32.653 --> 04:33.719
Me, too.

04:33.720 --> 04:34.987
Glen McKenna, neat.

04:35.089 --> 04:37.123
Nice order. Up top.

04:40.161 --> 04:43.363
Look, it's been 30 years.

04:43.364 --> 04:45.598
And now you just
show up out of nowhere?

04:45.599 --> 04:48.668
This is... this is going
to take me a minute.

04:48.669 --> 04:50.870
Yeah. I understand.

04:53.040 --> 04:55.241
By the way, hell of a tie.
Is that Italian silk?

04:55.242 --> 04:57.644
I love you, Daddy. I'm so glad
we're best friends now.

05:00.314 --> 05:01.765
- Make a muscle.
- There you go.

05:01.766 --> 05:02.882
Ah!

05:02.883 --> 05:05.085
Guys, my dad's awesome.

05:05.086 --> 05:06.820
He's the mother of all fathers.

05:06.821 --> 05:08.088
Check this out.

05:08.089 --> 05:10.023
Hey, back when I was a kid,
you used to be a roadie.

05:10.024 --> 05:13.093
- Do you still do that?
- Not anymore.

05:13.094 --> 05:16.396
Back in '83 I'm lugging amps for
The Stones through West Germany,

05:16.397 --> 05:18.565
and their tour manager
loses his arms,

05:18.566 --> 05:20.734
bus-surfing through a tunnel.

05:20.735 --> 05:21.868
Gnarly.

05:21.869 --> 05:24.070
Long story short,

05:24.071 --> 05:27.007
I've been managing tours
ever since,

05:27.008 --> 05:30.677
and that dude high-fives people
with his face now.

05:30.678 --> 05:33.663
You're funny.

05:33.664 --> 05:35.348
My dad's funny.

05:36.249 --> 05:38.417
So, all these years,
there's this one question

05:38.418 --> 05:40.036
I've been dying to ask him.

05:40.037 --> 05:42.455
- Why did you abandon me?
- Why'd you wait so long to contact me?

05:42.456 --> 05:45.058
You've hurt me before,
why should I trust you now?

05:46.159 --> 05:47.293
Do you...

05:47.494 --> 05:49.195
get laid a lot?

05:50.396 --> 05:51.664
Big-time.

05:54.733 --> 05:56.135
Observe.

